Former President Barack Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama expressed their condolences to former Vice President Walter Mondale and his family on the passing of Joan Adams Mondale. They recognized Joan as a devoted partner to her husband and a lifelong patron of the arts. Joan filled the Vice Presidential mansion and the U.S. embassy in Japan with works by various artists, including unknown ones. She also made significant contributions to the Federal Council on the Arts and Humanities and the Kennedy Center, advocating for the role of art in the nation and promoting understanding worldwide. The Obamas expressed their gratitude for Joan's service to the nation and offered their thoughts and prayers to the Mondale family.